# Lumen Backend

FastAPI service for the Lumen journaling PWA. Phase 1 complete.
Runs in Docker (lumen-api, port 8000).

## Stack
- Python 3.11, FastAPI 0.115, Pydantic v2, supabase-py 2.28, PyJWT, asyncpg 0.29
- Supabase async client for application queries; asyncpg pool for SQL/migrations
- No ORM. No TypeScript. No local installs — Docker only.

## File Map
- `app/main.py` — lifespan, CORS, routers
- `app/auth.py` — `get_current_user` (HTTPBearer, JWKS → HS256 fallbacks)
- `app/db.py` — asyncpg pool, schema snapshot, migrations, raw SQL
- `app/dependencies.py` — `get_supabase`, `get_db_pool`, `require_role(minimum_role)`
- `app/routes/entries.py` — user-scoped CRUD `/entries`
- `app/routes/users.py` — `GET /users/me`
- `app/routes/admin.py` — stats, user management, cross-user entries
- `app/routes/schema.py` — schema snapshot, migrations, raw SQL endpoints
- `app/models/entry.py` — entry Pydantic models + EntryListResponse
- `app/models/admin.py` — RoleUpdate, UserSummary, AdminStats
- `app/models/schema.py` — SchemaSnapshot, MigrationRecord, SQLRequest, SQLResponse
- `migrations/` — numbered `.sql` files, applied via `POST /admin/schema/migrations/apply`

## Auth
`get_current_user` uses `HTTPBearer` — shows Authorize button in Swagger UI.
Resolution: JWKS (asymmetric) → HS256 local secret → HS256 remote `/auth/v1/user`.
Returns `user_id` (JWT `sub`). Raises 401 on failure.

## RBAC
`require_role(minimum_role)` in `app/dependencies.py`.
Hierarchy: `user(1) < admin(2) < superuser(3)`. Checks `user_roles` table.
Returns caller `user_id` on pass, raises 403 on fail.

## Key Endpoint Permissions
- `/entries/*` — any authenticated user (own data only)
- `/users/me` — any authenticated user
- `/admin/stats`, `/admin/users`, `/admin/schema` — admin+
- `/admin/users/{id}/role`, `/admin/sql`, `/admin/schema/migrations/apply` — superuser only

## Environment Variables
Required: `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY`, `SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `DATABASE_URL`
- `DATABASE_URL` is a direct Postgres URI for asyncpg — URL-encode `@` in password as `%40`

Optional: `SUPABASE_JWKS_URL`, `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`

## Rules (non-negotiable)
- No ORM — Supabase client or asyncpg only
- No hardcoded secrets — all config from `.env`
- `user_id` always from JWT, never from request body
- Return 404 (not 403) for owned-resource-not-found
- Return 401 for missing/invalid JWT
- CORS: allow `http://localhost:3000`

## Out of Scope
Do not implement: frontend wiring (Phase 2), S3 (Phase 3), Lambda/Bedrock (Phase 4), Comprehend (Phase 5).
